Your ```handlePress``` syntax is wrong, since you are trying to replace the original Event Handler triggered with the *onPress* event.

This is the right syntax (if you want to refer to it into render method like what have you done):

```js
    handlePress = () =&gt; event =&gt; {
        console.log(this.props.number);
    };
```

It&#39;s like you are wrapping the original event handler with this new one.

This is a very powerful pattern, since with this you are able to avoid anonymous arrow functions into *render()*

You can read more about this lovely pattern here: https://medium.com/silesis/handle-events-in-react-with-arrow-functions-ede88184bbb

